1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated, Zeta Lambda Omega Chapter, on
3 the occasion of its one hundred eighteenth Founders' Day and seventy-first Charter
4 Day.
5 WHEREAS, Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated, was founded on January 15,
6 1908, on the campus of Howard University and is the oldest Greek-letter organization
7 established by African American college-educated women; and
8 WHEREAS, the Zeta Lambda Omega Chapter was chartered on February 26, 1955,
9 as the first graduate chapter of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated; the chapter is
10 based in Rapides Parish and has served Central Louisiana for seventy-one years through
11 scholarships, youth mentoring, health outreach, senior support programs, and civic
12 engagement; and
13 WHEREAS, the members of the Zeta Lambda Omega Chapter continue to partner
14 with schools, nonprofit organizations, and civic leaders to strengthen educational
15 opportunities, wellness initiatives, and leadership development for residents of Louisiana;
16 and
17 WHEREAS, 2026 marks the celebration of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority's one
18 hundred-eighteenth Founders' Day and the Zeta Lambda Omega Chapter's seventy-first
19 Charter Day; and
